There's no contract set in stone or anything.

00:51:33.520 --> 00:51:36.420
These people may well change their mind if it doesn't work for them.

00:51:36.560 --> 00:51:38.640
But my idea is, okay, they've shown interest.

00:51:39.260 --> 00:51:43.020
let's go headfirst into seeing whether we can help them

00:51:43.160 --> 00:51:44.620
and whether they'd be able to use NowWells.

00:51:44.920 --> 00:51:48.240
If it doesn't work out, we'll just have strengthened the NowWells API

